                            Embassy in Norway</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v03</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d43</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">43</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-03-12T19:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-03-12T19:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-03-12T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-03-12T19:00:00-05:00" n="43" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d43">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">857.20/3–1248: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Norway</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-03-12T19:00:00-05:00">March 12, 1948—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>107. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss>s 143 Mar 11, 6 p. m. and 146 Mar 12,
                    noon. You may inform <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> we are giving
                    most urgent consideration to question of Norwegian security. If Soviet demands
                    are made on Norway, in our opinion it is imperative that Norway adamantly resist
                    such demands and pressure. Events in Czecho and elsewhere demonstrate futility
                    of any other course. Soviet demands on Turkey and Iran were resolutely and
                    successfully resisted by those countries. The American Govt supported both
                    Turkey and Iran in resisting the Soviet demands.</p>
                <p>You may tell <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> in absolute confidence
                    that we are in communication with Brit Govt about Norwegian situation. You
                    should confer with your Brit colleague about advisability of correlating your
                    talks <pb facs="0070" n="52" xml:id="pg_52"/> with <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> with those of BritAmb who I am sure wall have received
                    instructions along this same line.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
